<div id="review_86488539" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/86488539" />
    <a title="Redsteve" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1858497-redsteve"><img alt="Redsteve" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1509664800p2/1858497.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/86488539?book_show_action=true">Jan 24, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Redsteve" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Redsteve" href="/user/show/1858497-redsteve">Redsteve</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780553290660" href="/book/show/2228266.Life_during_Wartime">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1858497-redsteve?shelf=caribbean">caribbean</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1858497-redsteve?shelf=mexico-central-america">mexico-central-america</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1858497-redsteve?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1858497-redsteve?shelf=weird-science">weird-science</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1858497-redsteve?shelf=war">war</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1858497-redsteve?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1858497-redsteve?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1858497-redsteve?shelf=cyberpunk">cyberpunk</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer86488539" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4207686050979607018">To me Shepard often feels as much a poet as a novelist, with a surprising ability to imbue the most squalid scenes with a sense of magic, or even myth. The future that he has created here is almost cyberpunk in its dystopian feel. But, rather than post-modern, his world seems connected to the past, especially the colonial and post-colonial evils in South and Central America. In the midst of high tech warfare and artificially-induced psychic powers, you get the feel of an interlocking series of m</span>
  <span id="freeText4207686050979607018" style="display:none">To me Shepard often feels as much a poet as a novelist, with a surprising ability to imbue the most squalid scenes with a sense of magic, or even myth. The future that he has created here is almost cyberpunk in its dystopian feel. But, rather than post-modern, his world seems connected to the past, especially the colonial and post-colonial evils in South and Central America. In the midst of high tech warfare and artificially-induced psychic powers, you get the feel of an interlocking series of magical folktales, both in the main plot, as well as in the stories told by various characters. As in many of Shepard's books, the protagonists are flawed (often deeply) and the deeper you get into the story, the stranger and more hallucinatory it becomes. This is my favorite Lucius Shepard novel, edging out Green Eyes by a hair. 5 stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4207686050979607018" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


