    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer683545932" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2554372939548009335">One of my favorite books of all. Lucius Shepard has the knack of writing personally for me. I&apos;m not saying he actually does this, but his phrasing, usage , what have you, always seems tailor-made for my enjoyment. I respond to it. Kind of hard to explain, but it gets under my skin (in a good way). This novel exhibits some of Mr. Shepard&apos;s strengths. He does exotic locales well. damaged protagonists, and elements of ..um...mysticism, for want of a better word. One of the few books I have reread, </span>
  <span id="freeText2554372939548009335" style="display:none">One of my favorite books of all. Lucius Shepard has the knack of writing personally for me. I'm not saying he actually does this, but his phrasing, usage , what have you, always seems tailor-made for my enjoyment. I respond to it. Kind of hard to explain, but it gets under my skin (in a good way). This novel exhibits some of Mr. Shepard's strengths. He does exotic locales well. damaged protagonists, and elements of ..um...mysticism, for want of a better word. One of the few books I have reread, and may do so again.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2554372939548009335" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
